The paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as morphological analysis and lemmatization, which are typically studied in the subfield of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The use of contextualized embeddings (BERT) and regularization techniques suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG, cs.AI), while the merging of corpora could also involve data management and processing (cs.NE) and potentially computer vision (cs.CV) if the corpora include image-based text.
